data.message: In recognition of going 180 days without a recordable accident, our Symmetry Malaysia facility has joined together to celebrate safety as a team.

The Japanese Orthopaedic Association (JOA) Annual Meeting is May 22-25th. Stop by the Symmetry Medical booth #3-10 to learn about our new innovative products and discuss how our strengths become your solutions.

Relay for Life of Kosciusko County was Saturday, May 17th. Over 330 community participants helped raise over $51,000! Congratulations to the Symmetry Medical Warsaw Team in your support and participation in the community event, it was a great place to take action and support the fight against cancer.

More than 4 million people in over 20 countries raise much-needed funds and awareness to save lives from cancer through the Relay For Life movement. Locate an event near you: http://bit.ly/1o1Ivx4.

Today is the Spring Blood Drive at the Symmetry Warsaw, IN location. Our Teammates blood donations help ensure lifesaving blood products are available for patients in need.

Visit the American Red Cross website to locate a blood drive near you: http://www.redcrossblood.org/. #redcross #ImProud2Give

Congratulations to Symmetry Warsaw teammate, Dave Gargis, in his successful year and graduation from the Kosciusko Leadership Academy. Dave sends a gracious 'Thank You' to Symmetry Medical for sponsoring him to join the Academy, providing him the opportunity to learn and grow his leadership within the county.

Dave's Academy team was selected to receive the Northenor Award this year. This $1,000 award was based on his team's Whitepaper project related to a Community Arts and Theatre Market Research Project. This project will help grow Fine Arts and the Wagon Wheel Theatre in Kosciusko County, Indiana.

Today is Earth Day! Earth Day is an annual event, celebrated on April 22, on which events are held worldwide to demonstrate support for environmental protection. How are you celebrating Earth Day this year?

data.message: Symmetry Surgical Introduces Symmetry(R) Sharp Kerrison. The Symmetry® Sharp Kerrison is a first-of-its-kind, patented surgical instrument designed with discerning surgeons and healthcare professionals in mind, providing a sharp tip every time. The Symmetry® Sharp Kerrison is the latest innovation in Symmetry Surgical's comprehensive Kerrison portfolio, which also features RapidClean®, convertible and take-apart designs.

Several teammates from the Symmetry Warsaw location teamed up with a local dog rescue organization, One Dog at a Time. The group is volunteering to support awareness and fundraising efforts to provide food and shelter for rescued dogs until they are adopted.
Great work everyone on supporting a local organization in need. For more information about One Dog at a Time, visit: www.odtr.org.

Have a story to share about your Symmetry teammates and local support efforts? Send us a message with details, we would love to hear about it.

Symmetry Medical Inc. sponsored the 1st Annual Exhibition VEX Robotics Tournament this weekend bringing engineering/technology and community elementary and high school youth teams together to battle their robotic creations in a regional competition. Congratulations to each of the talented teams for an exciting afternoon and a job well done!
Attending the #AAOS2014 Annual Meeting? Stop by our booth 4949 Hall G to learn about new product innovations & Total Solutions approach.

After 24 years (to the day) of successful and dedicated service with Symmetry Medical, Darin Martin is retiring today. Please join us in thanking Darin for his service and friendship over the years.  Darin plans to spend time with family and friends and enjoying classic car cruises, Harley rides, playing guitar, golf, writing, flying, and just more fun time on Lake Chapman. 
Happy retirement Darin!

EDITED: NOTICE FOR TEAMMATES OF SYMMETRY MEDICAL IN AVILLA, IN (1/7/14 @ 9:55 a.m.):
Noble County is currently under a “Warning” restricting travel to emergency personnel only. During a “Warning” local travel advisory, individuals are directed to refrain from all travel. The Warning is scheduled to expire at 12:00 p.m. on Tuesday, January 7, 2014.

PROVIDING THE WARNING EXPIRES AND IS DOWNGRADED TO A “Watch" or "Advisory”, Symmetry Medical Avilla will open beginning at 12:30 p.m. on Tuesday, 1-7-14.

* 1st shift may report to work at 12:30 p.m. Providing work is available in their specific work areas, teammates may work extra hours.
* 2nd shift will resume as normal at 2:00 p.m.

THIS SCHEDULE WILL ONLY APPLY IF THE “WARNING” IS DOWNGRADED TO A “Watch" or "Advisory”. Teammates should continue to monitor the following Internet sites to stay abreast of the travel levels, both in Noble County and in their county of residence:

http://www.in.gov/dhs/traveladvisory/
https://local.nixle.com/

data.message: Team holiday luncheon - over 400 teammates served!
Teammates at our Warsaw and Claypool Indiana locations celebrated a safety milestone today with a pizza party. Congrats to each of you!

Check out the photo collage below of the Symmetry Malaysia Team participating in the FMM Rock'n'Roll Futsal Tournament. 

Looks like a lot of fun!

Congratulations to the Teammates from the Symmetry Medical Malaysia facility who participated in the Penang Bridge International Marathon last week!

For information about this Marathon check out their website: http://www.penangmarathon.gov.my/portal/about-penang-bridge-marathon.

The Symmetry Medical Avilla location held a fun Halloween afternoon with a chili cook-off. 11 teammates participated. Awards for first and second place were awarded. Congrats to the winners!
Stay tuned for costume contest results (voting is still open).
Congratulations Warsaw and Claypool teammates who came out to support the American Red Cross Blood Drive this week. Together we collected 45 units of blood - way to go!

Symmetry Medical Warsaw Teammates participated in the 2013 Marine Mud Run held at Mishawaka Marian High School on Saturday, September 7th. 

It is the Marine Corps League, St Joseph Valley Det. 095’s Mission to help the children and their families who are struggling each year have a brighter Christmas and influence the lives of those children. Every toy brings hope to those children who have very little hope during the holiday season and shows them someone does care. Thus, with the support of the South Bend Marines, we are able to foster that hope through the Toys for Tots program; raising valuable dollars to help fill the void experienced each year within the Toys for Tots program in the age groups of 0-3 and 11- up thru the Marine Mud Run – 3.1 mile run through mud and obstacles.

Congrats to each of you for a job well done!
Great job everyone!

Symmetry Medical Avilla employees participated in the Kendallville Warrior Run 5K run for Team PRIDE.   
Team PRIDE, Inc., is dedicated to helping low-income children develop the values and confidence needed to avoid criminal behavior and to succeed in school and beyond. Team PRIDE will enable children involved in delinquency cases, abuse or neglect proceedings and special education to participate in "Karate for Kids" programs that offer mentorship and teach leadership skills and goal-setting to help them develop PRIDE (perseverance, respect, integrity, discipline, excellence) in themselves and in their lives.
Visit http://www.prideforkids.org/ for more information.

Today is the United Way of Caring in Kosciusko County, IN. This is a one-day event providing volunteers to give back to the community while making a positive impact on others.

Team Symmetry is participating with the fix-up/clean-up of single family homes occupied by: seniors with no access to assistance, lower income families and individuals with physical limitations.

Congrats to each of you who have participated and work to make an impact in the community! Contact your local United Way to inquire about supporting your local community impact efforts: http://www.unitedway.org/take-action/volunteer/

It's that time of year again for the Annual Company Picnic in Warsaw, IN. Symmetry families enjoyed the day at the Fort Wayne Children's Zoo. So many animals to learn about, rides to enjoy and more. 
Check out our photo from the Sky Safari - a great bird’s eye view of lions, zebras, wildebeest, and ostrich in the African Journey exhibit. What a great day it was!
Saturday marked the Annual Symmetry Golf Outing organized by our Warsaw, IN Teammates. Participants enjoyed a relaxing day of 18 holes, lunch and door prizes.
It's Symmetry Day at the Kosciusko County Fair today in Warsaw, IN! We are handing out 2,500 green/reusable bags today upon entrance. See you there!

After 35 successful and dedicated years with Symmetry Medical (and its predecessor, Othy, Inc.), Linda Scalet of Warsaw, IN, will be retiring this July. During Linda's long tenure she helped shape Symmetry into its current structure, starting with Othy changing into Symmetry, the merger with Mettis, and the IPO. Thereafter, she was a part of building the DDC, the acquisition of New Bedford and Avilla, and made trips to Specialty Surgical Instrumentation (now Symmetry Surgical) to help structure its HR department.

Linda has had a positive impact on our lives. Please join us in thanking Linda for her service over the years.
